    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION AXLES WITH CONTROLLED TRACTION
        DIFFERENTIALS: EATON - REASSEMBLE - CLUTCH PACK (HEAVY-DUTY)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="5">
        <title>CLUTCH PACK (HEAVY-DUTY)</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The clutch pack can be installed in gear support case with wheel differential assembled or
                    disassembled. With differential assembled, proceed as follows:
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Ring gear may fit loosely or have an interference fit on the gear support case. Proceed as
                    necessary to assemble ring gear to support case (Step 1 or 2).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">Install Ring Gear with Interference Fit.</emph>
                Place gear support case assembly on bench with clutch pack side down. Position ring gear (gear teeth up)
                on gear support case and align bolt holes. Temporarily install two ring gear bolts to assure alignment,
                then tap ring gear alternately on opposite sides with a soft-nosed hammer until gear is fully seated
                against gear support case flange. Turn assembly over, then place in press (gear teeth down) on hard wood
                blocks. Position blocks to the outside of the ring gear to allow clearance for installation of two
                alignment bolts. Install alignment bolts, then proceed with reassembly procedures in Step 3.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">Install Ring Gear with Loose Fit.</emph>
                Place ring gear in press (gear teeth down) on hard wood blocks. Position blocks to the outside of the
                ring gear to allow clearance for installation of the gear support case assembly and two alignment bolts.
                Place gear support case assembly in ring gear and align bolt holes. Install two alignment bolts in
                mounting holes, then proceed with reassembly procedures in Step 3.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install snap ring in snap ring groove of friction plate driver. Place friction plate driver
                (with snap ring down) in center of gear support case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401029">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401029" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401029" filename="../figg14/g1401029.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Install Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place one tanged friction plate over friction plate driver, positioning tangs into slots in
                gear support case. Brush top of friction plate with a generous application of axle lube. Refer to GROUP
                10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for recommended lubes. Place one splined friction
                plate over friction plate driver and brush top of this plate with lube (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401030">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401030" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401030" filename="../figg14/g1401030.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Place One Splined Friction Plate Over Friction Plate Driver</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat procedures in Step 4 until there is an equal amount of friction plates of each
                (tanged and splined) mounted on the friction plate driver (see note below).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Heavy-duty CTD clutch pack friction plates vary with axle models.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place last tanged friction plate and pressure plate over friction plate driver. Then using a
                press and suitable adapters, compress clutch pack and install round snap ring in groove of friction
                plate driver (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401031">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401031" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401031" filename="../figg14/g1401031.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Install Round Snap Ring in Groove of Friction Plate Driver</caption>
            </figure>
