        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, press bearing cone on gear support case cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place compression springs in smallest possible circle on pressure plate. Place gear support
                case cover over springs and temporarily install two alignment bolts. Reach through hole in gear support
                case cover and move compression springs radially outward as far as they will go (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401032">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401032" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401032" filename="../figg14/g1401032.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Move Compression Springs Radially Outward as Far as They Will Go</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress springs until gear case cover bottoms against gear support case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1401033">Figure 33</hotlnk>). With press pressure still applied, install ring gear
                bolts (all bolt heads on ring gear side) and locknuts. Remove assembly from press, then tighten locknuts
                to 195 to 245 ft-lbs. (264 to 332 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1401033" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401033" filename="../figg14/g1401033.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Compress Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
